				 Facebook Christmas ruin
 SALLY PECK																								London, Nov. 26: While recent headlines have been dominated by leaks of personal information by the British government, it turns out that social networking websites might also be spilling personal details  like what users have bought for Christmas  sparking cries that Facebook might ruin the festive season.																								The social networking sites use of Beacon, an advertising system that exploits word-of-mouth marketing, has angered Facebook users by publicising details of their online shopping habits. 																								Moveon.org, the liberal US-based political pressure group, is waging a campaign against Facebook, saying the site violates privacy by sharing details of books, films and other holiday gifts purchased online. 																								Matthew Helfgott, 20, one of the 20,000 signatories of MoveOns petition, wrote: I saw my gf [girlfriend] bought an item I had been saying I wanted... so now part of my christmas gift has been ruined. 																								Facebook is ruining Christmas!					 THE DAILY TELEGRAPH
